### Describe the feature

Rename audio devices from chromium to Teams for Linux

### Motivation

When you open the volume mixer they all say `chromium` instead of `Teams for Linux`

I also noticed when you're on a call it creates 4 playback streams but far as I can tell only one is ever used.

`/etc/pipewire/pipewire-pulse.conf.d/50-teams-for-linux.conf`
```
# Set the application name for Teams for Linux audio streams.
# Without this, Electron/Chromium hardcodes "Chromium" in the mixer.
pulse.rules = [
  {
    matches = [
      {
        application.process.binary = "teams-for-linux"
      }
    ]
    actions = {
      update-props = {
        application.name  = "Teams for Linux"
      }
    }
  }
]
```

### Alternatives

I tried various methods in the electron code but I couldn't workout how to do it. Not sure if it's a limitation of Electron itself perphas.

